CABLE: Comcast Corp. agreed to buy an interest in Pay-Per-View Network Inc. 's Viewer's Choice, a cable programming service owned by eight other cable and entertainment concerns.
Financial terms weren't disclosed, but Viewer's Choice said Comcast would be the ninth equal holder. 

NEWSPAPERS: United Newspapers PLC's advertising periodicals division acquired Pacific Media Group Inc. of California for an initial $25 million.
It will pay $5 million more if Pacific's pretax profits for the six-month period ending Dec. 31 exceed certain undisclosed targets. 

